  "prompt": "How can you tell if your cat loves you?",
  "response": "Here are some signs that your cat loves you:\n\n1. Physical signs of affection\n- Purring when near you\n- Rubbing against you\n- Kneading you with their paws\n- Slow blinking (often called \"cat kisses\")\n- Sleeping near or on you\n\n2. Behavioral signs\n- Following you around the house\n- Greeting you when you come home\n- Showing you their belly (a sign of trust)\n- Bringing you \"gifts\" like toys or small prey\n- Choosing to spend time in your presence\n\n3. Communication signs\n- Meowing or chirping at you\n- Holding their tail upright when you're around\n- Showing their tail's \"question mark\" shape when near you\n\n4. Grooming behaviors\n- Licking you\n- Trying to groom you like they would another cat\n\n5. Body language\n- Relaxed posture around you\n- No signs of aggression or fear\n- Ears facing forward\n- Soft, calm facial expression\n\nRemember, cats show love differently from dogs, and each cat has a unique personality. Some cats are more demonstrative than others.",
